The paper focuses on a method for automatically learning test case selection and prioritization in Continuous Integration (CI) using reinforcement learning. This involves selecting and prioritizing test cases based on their duration, previous last execution, and failure history. The paper also mentions the constantly changing environment of CI, where new test cases are created and obsolete test cases are deleted. These aspects suggest that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the use of reinforcement learning indicates a focus on Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of a reward function, which suggests a focus on Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.SE, followed by cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.PL, and cs.SE.
